            {
              "name": "Get Current User",
              "request": {
                "auth": {
                  "type": "bearer",
                  "bearer": [
                    {
                      "key": "token",
                      "value": "{{accessToken}}",
                      "type": "string"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [
                  {
                    "key": "Authorization",
                    "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}"
                  }
                ],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/me",
                  "host": [
                    "{{baseUrl}}"
                  ],
                  "path": [
                    "api",
                    "v1",
                    "auth",
                    "me"
                  ]
                },
                "description": "## Purpose\n\nReturns the currently authenticated user (\"me\") based on the access token provided.\n\nUse this endpoint to:\n\n- Verify that an `accessToken` is valid\n    \n- Retrieve the user profile for the logged-in account\n    \n- Confirm role/active status for authorization checks in clients\n    \n\n## Authentication\n\n**Required:** Bearer token\n\nThe request sends:\n\n- Header: `Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}`\n    \n\nIf the token is missing, invalid, or expired, the API should return an authentication error (commonly `401`).\n\n## Variables used\n\n- `{{baseUrl}}` — Base URL of the KVHS API (e.g., `https://api.your-domain.com`)\n    \n- `{{accessToken}}` — JWT / access token returned from the login endpoint\n    \n\n## Request\n\n- **Method:** `GET`\n    \n- **URL:** `{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/me`\n    \n- **Headers:**\n    \n    - `Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}`\n        \n- **Body:** none\n    \n\n## Successful response (200)\n\nExample response body:\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"id\": 1,\n  \"email\": \"tina@kvsh.com\",\n  \"name\": \"Ngen Tina\",\n  \"role\": \"admin\",\n  \"is_active\": true\n}\n\n ```\n\nField notes:\n\n- `id` (number): User identifier\n    \n- `email` (string): User email address\n    \n- `name` (string): Display/name of the user\n    \n- `role` (string): User role (e.g., `admin`)\n    \n- `is_active` (boolean): Whether the account is active\n    \n\n## Common error responses\n\n- **400 Bad Request**: Malformed request (uncommon for this endpoint)\n    \n- **401 Unauthorized**: Missing/invalid/expired token\n    \n- **403 Forbidden**: Token is valid but user lacks permission (role/authorization)\n    \n- **404 Not Found**: Endpoint not found (wrong baseUrl/path)\n    \n- **500 Internal Server Error**: Unexpected server error\n    \n\n## Notes\n\n- Ensure your active environment (e.g., `kvhs`) contains valid values for `baseUrl` and `accessToken` before sending this request."
              },
              "response": []
            }
          ]
        },
